Yes, so I need to ask you
to get this done by tomorrow.

00:21:23.763 --> 00:21:25.515
That place over there is amazing.

00:21:28.643 --> 00:21:29.727
No, him.

00:21:32.313 --> 00:21:33.606
It wasn't me.

00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:36.400
He needed it in
Hamchorong Batang Extended Bold.

00:21:37.276 --> 00:21:38.277
Bold.

00:21:42.115 --> 00:21:43.324
Go on.

00:21:47.161 --> 00:21:48.955
He's worse than those TV station guys.

00:21:49.038 --> 00:21:50.665
I thought you were
going to punch him, bro.

00:21:50.748 --> 00:21:53.126
That's why I sent him away quickly.

00:21:53.209 --> 00:21:54.377
It was a close call.

00:21:54.460 --> 00:21:55.294
Good call.

00:21:55.378 --> 00:21:57.088
If you punch guys like him,
all you get is a sore fist.

00:22:01.509 --> 00:22:02.343
Oh, damn.

00:22:04.178 --> 00:22:05.513
Why is that Hamchorong guy still here?

00:22:06.889 --> 00:22:09.600
-Something's off about him.
-Why is he doing this to us?

00:22:09.684 --> 00:22:10.852
Should I ward him off?

00:22:10.935 --> 00:22:13.646
-He's so weird.
-Seriously.

00:22:13.729 --> 00:22:15.398
I know I've seen him before.

00:22:17.108 --> 00:22:18.818
"Good Detective Kang Pil-gu"?

00:22:18.901 --> 00:22:22.196
What kind of title is that?
His name’s just as weird.

00:22:37.378 --> 00:22:39.922
Wow, this punk…

00:22:42.049 --> 00:22:43.092
He's a genius.

00:22:57.899 --> 00:22:59.609
Damn it! What the hell?

00:23:02.069 --> 00:23:04.447
Could you change it to
Hamchorong Batang Extended Bold instead?

00:23:04.530 --> 00:23:07.742
Hamchorong?
Have you lost your mind, you punk?

00:23:07.825 --> 00:23:09.202
You nearly gave me a heart attack!

00:23:09.911 --> 00:23:10.870
I remember now.

00:23:13.122 --> 00:23:14.123
What do you mean?

00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:17.251
I knew I'd seen you before.

00:23:17.335 --> 00:23:19.295
But I couldn't remember
even when I got home,

00:23:19.378 --> 00:23:22.298
or even after I walked my dog
and took out the recyclables.

00:23:22.381 --> 00:23:23.633
I was about to lose my damn mind.

00:23:23.716 --> 00:23:25.760
But as soon as I lay down to sleep,

00:23:26.385 --> 00:23:27.220
I remembered.

00:23:28.512 --> 00:23:29.931
That movie, Sad Waltz.

00:23:30.598 --> 00:23:32.099
You're an actor!

00:23:33.643 --> 00:23:36.145
You came all the way back here
just to confirm that?

00:23:36.229 --> 00:23:37.188
No.

00:23:37.897 --> 00:23:38.981
I'm here to cast you.

00:23:41.651 --> 00:23:42.777
Jeez.

00:23:42.860 --> 00:23:46.322
I want you to be in my movie,
Good Detective Kang Pil-gu,

00:23:46.405 --> 00:23:49.367
as the main character,
Detective Kang Pil-gu.

00:24:00.878 --> 00:24:01.879
Let's go.

00:24:01.963 --> 00:24:02.922
Damn!

00:24:05.174 --> 00:24:06.092
GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

00:24:07.551 --> 00:24:08.719
Hurry, let's go.

00:24:12.098 --> 00:24:14.642
Hey, move! We're busy.

00:24:14.725 --> 00:24:15.685
Come on.

00:24:15.768 --> 00:24:17.645
Move it! We're busy!

00:24:18.271 --> 00:24:20.481
You're saying the color bled?

00:24:21.107 --> 00:24:22.316
And I told him…

00:24:24.026 --> 00:24:25.278
Hello there!

00:24:25.861 --> 00:24:27.863
We'll get it reprinted for you.

00:24:27.947 --> 00:24:29.282
Yes, of course.

00:24:37.290 --> 00:24:39.083
What the hell, man?

00:24:39.166 --> 00:24:41.335
Mr. Leading Man,
are you just getting off work?

00:24:41.919 --> 00:24:43.087
Come on, seriously?

00:24:43.713 --> 00:24:44.880
What are you doing here?

00:24:44.964 --> 00:24:47.091
-Go home already!
-I'll go after you take this.

00:24:47.174 --> 00:24:48.467
Why are you here? Go away!

00:24:48.551 --> 00:24:50.970
Mr. Leading Man,
would you please just consider…

00:24:51.053 --> 00:24:52.722
I told you no already. Go away!

00:24:52.805 --> 00:24:53.931
You didn't have to lock the door.

00:24:54.015 --> 00:24:57.560
-There's no point in staying here. Go!
-Just help me out this once.

00:24:59.020 --> 00:25:00.062
Mr. Leading Man.

00:25:01.397 --> 00:25:02.481
Seriously?

00:25:02.565 --> 00:25:04.650
-I'm about to lose it.
-Mr. Leading Man?

00:25:04.734 --> 00:25:06.235
No, stop calling me that!

00:25:06.319 --> 00:25:07.737
Don't call me that, all right?

00:25:07.820 --> 00:25:10.656
Mr. Lim, I really want you in my movie.

00:25:11.490 --> 00:25:13.367
You go to a great school.

00:25:13.451 --> 00:25:15.619
There must be a truckload of good actors
to choose from.

00:25:15.703 --> 00:25:17.621
What makes you think
you can trust me with that role?

00:25:17.705 --> 00:25:21.542
I get that it's just a graduation project,
but you can't afford to fail.

00:25:21.625 --> 00:25:23.210
I'm doing this
to make sure it's a success.

00:25:24.879 --> 00:25:25.880
Fine.

00:25:27.298 --> 00:25:28.924
Let me ask you then.

00:25:29.008 --> 00:25:31.886
Why do you want me
to play that aggressive detective?

00:25:32.470 --> 00:25:33.804
Because you'll do a great job!

00:25:34.430 --> 00:25:37.475
I'm not good at explaining things,
but that's why.

00:25:37.558 --> 00:25:39.268
I can make it happen.

00:25:39.352 --> 00:25:41.979
I'm confident that I can,
if you'll just let me.

00:25:43.314 --> 00:25:45.775
I saw that there's
a ton of chase and fight scenes.

00:25:45.858 --> 00:25:47.485
I can't even fight!

00:25:47.568 --> 00:25:50.946
Pacifism runs in my DNA,
right down to the bone.

00:25:51.030 --> 00:25:52.198
I'm busy, so go away.

00:25:52.281 --> 00:25:53.324
Go away now!

00:25:54.700 --> 00:25:57.078
Wait, you can't just throw that around!

00:25:57.161 --> 00:25:58.371
Please handle it with care.

00:25:58.954 --> 00:26:01.040
Goodness, Mr. Hwang. Don't drink too much.

00:26:01.123 --> 00:26:03.334
Yes, thank you.

00:26:07.129 --> 00:26:09.590
Come on, just do it.

00:26:10.174 --> 00:26:12.009
Why are you being so difficult?

00:26:12.093 --> 00:26:15.262
How many people would actually watch
an indie film made by a college student?

00:26:15.346 --> 00:26:16.347
-For goodness' sake.
-Well,

00:26:16.430 --> 00:26:20.184
what if someone watches it
and I end up being humiliated?

00:26:20.267 --> 00:26:24.438
And why bother
if nobody's going to watch it anyway?

00:26:27.358 --> 00:26:29.068
You know, I read the script too.

00:26:31.195 --> 00:26:32.696
A story like that is rare to come by.

00:26:32.780 --> 00:26:35.783
Look, forget the fact
that the director is inexperienced.

00:26:35.866 --> 00:26:38.369
It's the kind of story that makes you
want to get right onto the set.

00:26:38.452 --> 00:26:40.371
Tell me, is it not?

00:26:42.164 --> 00:26:44.500
-It is.
-See?

00:26:49.380 --> 00:26:53.092
Hey, remember when I was doing stage plays
and got recruited by the agency?

00:26:53.843 --> 00:26:55.261
You were my first manager.

00:26:55.344 --> 00:26:56.387
Right.

00:26:56.971 --> 00:26:58.264
How was I back then?

00:26:59.640 --> 00:27:00.474
You, bro?

00:27:01.350 --> 00:27:02.977
You were…

00:27:03.477 --> 00:27:04.478
different.

00:27:07.731 --> 00:27:09.775
You had the potential to be a top star.

00:27:09.859 --> 00:27:10.776
Yeah, right.

00:27:15.156 --> 00:27:17.283
If only you hadn't dated Gwon Se-na,

00:27:17.867 --> 00:27:20.077
you wouldn't have ended up like this.

00:27:20.828 --> 00:27:24.832
That ungrateful little wench.

00:27:24.915 --> 00:27:29.003
You broke up with her for her sake,
and she should be thankful for that.

00:27:29.086 --> 00:27:31.213
Instead, she lied just to save face.

00:27:33.716 --> 00:27:35.384
What's with that look?

00:27:35.468 --> 00:27:38.262
Don't tell me you think
this indie film could suddenly turn you

00:27:38.345 --> 00:27:41.182
into a world-famous movie star
or something.

00:27:41.682 --> 00:27:42.766
I never said I was thinking that!

00:27:44.059 --> 00:27:45.895
-Jeez, whatever.
-Why would you say that?

00:27:45.978 --> 00:27:47.646
No need to get so angry.

00:27:50.774 --> 00:27:51.734
Hey.

00:27:51.817 --> 00:27:55.237
We started this print shop
with our bare hands

00:27:55.321 --> 00:27:56.489
and made a name for ourselves.

00:27:56.572 --> 00:27:57.781
Things are pretty good now, no?

00:27:58.574 --> 00:28:00.618
Some people don't make
half as much as you do,

00:28:00.701 --> 00:28:02.953
but they still buy cars,
play golf, and live it up.

00:28:03.037 --> 00:28:04.705
But what do you do for yourself?

00:28:05.289 --> 00:28:09.460
Just think of it as a hobby.

00:28:09.543 --> 00:28:13.088
You deserve to do what you want
every now and then.

00:28:13.881 --> 00:28:16.258
Don't worry
about the print shop, all right?

00:28:16.342 --> 00:28:17.384
Leave it to me.

00:28:17.968 --> 00:28:19.512
Imperial Print!

00:28:36.529 --> 00:28:38.948
MR. LEADING MAN,
I'LL ASK YOU ONE LAST TIME.

00:28:39.031 --> 00:28:41.909
PLEASE BE IN MY MOVIE.
IF YOU TURN ME DOWN AGAIN, I'LL STOP.

00:28:41.992 --> 00:28:44.703
BUT I URGE THAT YOU CONSIDER IT
WITH A POSITIVE MINDSET.

00:28:58.008 --> 00:28:59.969
Will I get paid?

00:29:05.432 --> 00:29:08.686
"He spins the handcuffs
and swiftly fastens them onto X's wrists."

00:29:10.896 --> 00:29:13.399
"They say you can't fix people."

00:29:14.483 --> 00:29:15.401
"But…

00:29:16.485 --> 00:29:17.778
I do."

00:29:18.445 --> 00:29:21.740
"Then he collapses, sprawling next to X."

00:29:22.491 --> 00:29:25.119
All right,
we'll wrap up our table read here.

00:29:26.287 --> 00:29:27.162
Good job.

00:29:28.080 --> 00:29:29.081
Good work, everyone.

00:29:34.753 --> 00:29:37.006
Can I have a word with you?

00:29:37.631 --> 00:29:38.549
Sure.

00:29:59.987 --> 00:30:02.448
I overdid it earlier, didn't I?

00:30:06.452 --> 00:30:08.329
-Mr. Lim.
-Yes?

00:30:08.412 --> 00:30:11.248
Let me start by saying
that what I'm about to tell you

00:30:11.332 --> 00:30:14.209
is meant for the sake of the movie,
and not to teach or lecture you.

00:30:14.293 --> 00:30:17.171
Of course. Feel free to say whatever.

00:30:17.254 --> 00:30:19.840
Don't be shy. Just tell me.

00:30:19.923 --> 00:30:20.966
Before I do that,

00:30:21.050 --> 00:30:23.344
I think we should decide on
how to address each other

00:30:23.427 --> 00:30:25.429
as a sign of respect
for our respective roles.

00:30:25.512 --> 00:30:27.139
Right. I see.

00:30:28.349 --> 00:30:29.183
Okay.

00:30:30.476 --> 00:30:32.061
You're right. Sounds good.

00:30:33.771 --> 00:30:34.938
Sounds good, Director.

00:30:36.982 --> 00:30:38.150
Mr. Lim.

00:30:38.233 --> 00:30:40.778
How did you analyze the character?

00:30:41.862 --> 00:30:43.155
Well…

00:30:43.238 --> 00:30:46.116
He thinks violence
is the only way to deal with criminals.

00:30:47.576 --> 00:30:50.621
And I think he has a troublemaker streak.

00:30:52.790 --> 00:30:53.707
Sir.

00:30:55.125 --> 00:30:58.545
How do you feel about him
fighting violence with violence?

00:30:59.588 --> 00:31:02.966
Wouldn't it depend
on the level of violence?

00:31:03.050 --> 00:31:05.094
On a case-by-case basis, no?

00:31:05.177 --> 00:31:06.804
So his approach depends on the situation?

00:31:10.265 --> 00:31:12.267
You're right. It shows in your acting.

00:31:12.851 --> 00:31:15.312
It screams,
"I don't know if I'm doing this right,

00:31:15.396 --> 00:31:19.274
but I'm trying to make the punching
and beating as natural as possible."

00:31:19.358 --> 00:31:22.236
This character values his fists
over the law. Why?

00:31:22.319 --> 00:31:25.197
Because his beliefs were
shaped by childhood experiences.

00:31:25.280 --> 00:31:28.701
That's why this character feels no guilt
beating up bad guys.

00:31:28.784 --> 00:31:30.536
To make this character authentic,

00:31:30.619 --> 00:31:32.830
you have to fully trust
that your beliefs are right.

00:31:32.913 --> 00:31:35.332
You have to become one with the character.

00:31:41.296 --> 00:31:42.423
Yes, sir.

00:31:42.506 --> 00:31:44.925
GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU

00:31:46.176 --> 00:31:47.261
Bro, what are you doing?

00:31:48.387 --> 00:31:50.013
We're swamped right now.

00:31:50.097 --> 00:31:51.890
-Hurry up and drop off the orders.
-Okay.

00:31:56.937 --> 00:31:58.856
They say you can't fix people.

00:31:58.939 --> 00:32:00.524
But I do.

00:32:00.607 --> 00:32:01.525
But I do.

00:32:01.608 --> 00:32:03.610
But I do!

00:32:03.694 --> 00:32:04.611
But I do!

00:32:07.698 --> 00:32:08.532
Stop right there!

00:32:10.159 --> 00:32:11.952
But I do.

00:32:29.344 --> 00:32:30.345
Stop right there!

00:32:31.722 --> 00:32:32.556
Stop.

00:32:34.600 --> 00:32:35.476
Stop!

00:32:36.101 --> 00:32:37.311
Stop right there!

00:32:50.282 --> 00:32:51.116
Cut!

00:32:55.370 --> 00:32:56.872
Has he lost his damn mind?

00:32:58.332 --> 00:33:00.584
Who shoots a chase scene for three days?

00:33:04.087 --> 00:33:05.172
Two and a half days, actually.

00:33:06.048 --> 00:33:09.259
The only expression captured on camera
is total exhaustion.

00:33:11.720 --> 00:33:14.890
Maybe it's because Kang Pil-gu
is damn exhausted.

00:33:15.432 --> 00:33:16.266
Right, sir?

00:33:16.350 --> 00:33:17.601
Wrong. Sure, it's hard.

00:33:17.684 --> 00:33:20.187
But he has to show he's determined
to catch the bastard

00:33:20.687 --> 00:33:22.105
and beat the hell out of him.

00:33:23.190 --> 00:33:24.191
Let's go again.

00:33:32.574 --> 00:33:35.077
Ready. Action!

00:33:37.663 --> 00:33:38.789
Cut!

00:33:38.872 --> 00:33:39.706
Action!

00:33:41.124 --> 00:33:42.668
Cut!

00:33:42.751 --> 00:33:43.585
Action!

00:33:47.965 --> 00:33:48.882
You okay?

00:33:50.217 --> 00:33:51.176
Don't stop.

00:33:51.260 --> 00:33:53.804
Keep acting until I say cut.

00:33:59.309 --> 00:34:01.436
All right, let's go again.

00:34:01.520 --> 00:34:02.396
Ready!

00:34:03.188 --> 00:34:04.189
Action!

00:34:10.821 --> 00:34:12.948
Cut.

00:34:18.412 --> 00:34:19.872
Mr. Lim, let's go again.

00:34:23.458 --> 00:34:24.376
That bastard.

00:34:28.088 --> 00:34:29.339
Ready. Action!

00:34:32.342 --> 00:34:35.220
-What?
-Cut.

00:34:35.304 --> 00:34:36.388
Damn it.

00:34:40.642 --> 00:34:42.436
-You did great.
-Thank you.

00:34:51.904 --> 00:34:53.488
Let's call it a day for the shoot.

00:34:57.743 --> 00:34:59.077
But we're not done yet.

00:35:00.287 --> 00:35:02.539
It seems you didn't fully prepare
for the character,

00:35:02.623 --> 00:35:06.710
so we'll stop filming today
and reshoot this later.

00:35:07.669 --> 00:35:08.837
-Clear the set, please.
-But…

00:35:08.921 --> 00:35:10.672
Hey, hold on a second!

00:35:11.548 --> 00:35:13.967
Are you out of your mind, Director?

00:35:14.051 --> 00:35:16.511
This isn't some multi-billion-won
budget movie!

00:35:16.595 --> 00:35:19.765
It's an indie film, so shoot it like one!

00:35:19.848 --> 00:35:21.516
Why can't you be reasonable about this?

00:35:21.600 --> 00:35:24.061
Why can't you read the room
or know your limits?

00:35:24.144 --> 00:35:26.146
Are you taking this
to the Cannes Film Festival?

00:35:26.229 --> 00:35:28.231
Not even Bong Joon-ho
or Park Chan-wook would go this far!

00:35:29.733 --> 00:35:30.734
How would you know that?

00:35:30.817 --> 00:35:34.863
It's not like you've worked with
those directors either, Mr. Lim.

00:35:34.947 --> 00:35:36.531
What did you just say?

00:35:36.615 --> 00:35:38.158
Get over here!

00:35:38.241 --> 00:35:40.619
Why you little…

00:35:40.702 --> 00:35:43.372
I've been speaking to you respectfully
and showing you respect as the director!

00:35:43.455 --> 00:35:45.874
You were practically begging me
to be in your movie,

00:35:45.958 --> 00:35:48.377
so I agreed
to be in your movie without pay!

00:35:48.460 --> 00:35:50.087
So how dare you say that to me?

00:35:50.754 --> 00:35:52.506
Had I known you were so bad at acting,

00:35:52.589 --> 00:35:54.716
I wouldn't have persuaded you.

00:35:57.636 --> 00:35:58.720
Is that so?

00:35:58.804 --> 00:36:01.223
So you have a death wish, is that it?

00:36:02.307 --> 00:36:04.851
Let's see how well you do on your own.

00:36:04.935 --> 00:36:06.228
I'm out!

00:36:14.027 --> 00:36:15.445
Cut. Again.

00:36:17.948 --> 00:36:19.574
-What?
-Cut. Again.

00:36:19.658 --> 00:36:21.702
Moving on to the next shot. Ready!

00:36:22.577 --> 00:36:23.495
Action!

00:36:25.539 --> 00:36:26.790
-What?
-Cut!

00:36:26.873 --> 00:36:28.458
All right. Ready.

00:36:29.084 --> 00:36:30.043
Action!

00:36:33.672 --> 00:36:34.756
What?

00:36:34.840 --> 00:36:36.508
It's all your fault, Detective Kang!

00:36:36.591 --> 00:36:37.467
Let's go again!

00:36:37.551 --> 00:36:39.177
Damn it, not again!

00:37:03.577 --> 00:37:04.411
You punk!

00:37:36.818 --> 00:37:38.904
They say you can't fix people.

00:37:40.906 --> 00:37:41.782
But…

00:37:45.118 --> 00:37:46.369
I do.

00:37:51.208 --> 00:37:52.751
Cut! Okay!

00:37:52.834 --> 00:37:54.544
-We're done!
-Yes!

00:37:54.628 --> 00:37:57.464
And that's a wrap
for Good Detective Kang Pil-gu!

00:37:57.547 --> 00:37:59.299
Good work, everyone!

00:38:07.307 --> 00:38:09.351
Everyone, please fill your glass.

00:38:11.019 --> 00:38:14.898
Thank you for all your hard work
while filming Good Detective Kang Pil-gu.

00:38:14.981 --> 00:38:17.150
Make sure to fill your bellies today!

00:38:19.402 --> 00:38:21.154
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

00:38:21.238 --> 00:38:23.949
-Cheers.
-Drink up!

00:38:24.032 --> 00:38:25.158
Drink…

00:38:29.329 --> 00:38:31.373
It's finally over.

00:38:31.957 --> 00:38:32.833
Mr. Lim.

00:38:33.416 --> 00:38:37.254
I know that I gave you
a really hard time while filming.

00:38:37.337 --> 00:38:39.256
It's all my fault.

00:38:39.339 --> 00:38:41.925
I know you're probably upset with me,

00:38:42.008 --> 00:38:45.887
but I hope you'll accept this drink
and forget about it.

00:38:47.389 --> 00:38:48.640
Hey.

00:38:59.693 --> 00:39:00.569
Drink up.

00:39:00.652 --> 00:39:02.737
Big applause for our leading man!

00:39:04.781 --> 00:39:07.576
-Lim Hyeon-jun!
-Lim Hyeon-jun!

00:39:07.659 --> 00:39:11.371
-Lim Hyeon-jun!
-Lim Hyeon-jun!

00:39:11.454 --> 00:39:14.791
