00:41:12.492 --> 00:41:13.702
What the hell?

00:41:13.785 --> 00:41:15.078
Are you taking this out?

00:41:15.578 --> 00:41:18.707
I just started it up
to keep the battery from dying out.

00:41:19.499 --> 00:41:20.583
I mean,

00:41:20.667 --> 00:41:24.254
I paid for this car myself,
so why can't I use it whenever I want?

00:41:24.337 --> 00:41:27.173
Come on, everyone's watching you.

00:41:27.966 --> 00:41:30.427
Take the company car
if you have a work appointment.

00:41:30.510 --> 00:41:34.889
I need to play roles like a wealthy heir,
a successful lawyer, or a doctor.

00:41:34.973 --> 00:41:38.310
That way, I won't look so out of place
driving a fancy car like that.

00:41:38.393 --> 00:41:41.229
I'm always playing broke detectives.

00:41:41.313 --> 00:41:44.107
No wonder people are shocked
when they see me in a car like that!

00:41:44.649 --> 00:41:46.776
People don't see the real me anymore.

00:41:46.860 --> 00:41:48.528
All they see is Detective Kang Pil-gu.

00:41:48.611 --> 00:41:51.031
These days, I even mistake my own name
for Kang Pil-gu

00:41:51.656 --> 00:41:53.074
instead of Lim Hyeon-jun.

00:41:53.158 --> 00:41:54.534
All right, I get it.

00:41:54.617 --> 00:41:57.912
Let's make sure your next project
reshapes your public image, bro.

00:41:58.705 --> 00:42:01.666
Let's please make that happen, Mr. Hwang.

00:42:03.043 --> 00:42:05.670
And don't call me "bro" in public.

00:42:07.172 --> 00:42:10.008
But why? You are my big bro.

00:42:10.091 --> 00:42:13.011
If you call me bro, it makes me look old.

00:42:13.094 --> 00:42:15.388
Shouldn't a CEO like you
manage his actor's public image?

00:42:15.972 --> 00:42:16.931
Seriously?

00:42:17.015 --> 00:42:18.892
What about my public image, then?

00:42:22.479 --> 00:42:24.481
Damn.

00:42:24.564 --> 00:42:26.608
You have a great body.

00:42:26.691 --> 00:42:29.152
Come to my room. I'll tip you really well.

00:42:29.235 --> 00:42:31.404
You pretty little thing.

00:42:33.073 --> 00:42:34.783
-Hands off.
-What?

00:42:35.700 --> 00:42:36.534
Get lost.

00:42:38.703 --> 00:42:41.206
Man, what's the matter with her?

00:42:45.210 --> 00:42:47.796
Her name is Wi Jeong-sin,
and she's 36 years old.

00:42:47.879 --> 00:42:49.881
She's been with Eunseongilbo for 12 years.

00:42:49.964 --> 00:42:52.133
She's currently
the political desk's ace reporter.

00:42:53.718 --> 00:42:56.471
She entered and graduated top of her class
in Media and Communication.

00:42:56.554 --> 00:42:58.556
She speaks English, Chinese, and Arabic

00:42:58.640 --> 00:43:00.141
and is fluent in all four languages.

00:43:00.767 --> 00:43:02.602
Known for her incredible mental toughness,

00:43:02.685 --> 00:43:05.146
she discovered crucial evidence
before the police

00:43:05.230 --> 00:43:07.482
at a murder scene
involving a dismembered body

00:43:07.565 --> 00:43:10.527
that made even a 20-year veteran detective
vomit and pass out.

00:43:11.027 --> 00:43:14.155
She also climbed a 100-meter tower crane
to interview protestors

00:43:14.239 --> 00:43:16.533
and played a key role in getting

00:43:16.616 --> 00:43:18.827
all unfairly dismissed
construction workers reinstated.

00:43:21.913 --> 00:43:23.748
As a war correspondent,

00:43:23.832 --> 00:43:27.168
she was the first in the world to report
the horrors of the Serian Civil War.

00:43:36.886 --> 00:43:39.264
After being caught in a bomb blast

00:43:39.347 --> 00:43:42.016
that nearly led
to the amputation of her leg,

00:43:42.100 --> 00:43:43.726
she had major surgery and barely survived.

00:43:45.645 --> 00:43:48.898
And she became the youngest recipient of
the Korean Journalist of the Year award.

00:43:48.982 --> 00:43:51.568
The Korean Journalist of the Year award
goes to Ms. Wi Jeong-sin.

00:43:54.112 --> 00:43:56.489
KOREAN JOURNALIST OF THE YEAR
AWARD CEREMONY

00:43:56.573 --> 00:43:59.284
ONNURI JOURNALISTS ASSOCIATION

00:44:02.579 --> 00:44:04.164
KOREAN JOURNALIST OF THE YEAR AWARD
WI JEONG-SIN

00:44:04.247 --> 00:44:05.081
DESK CHIEF
YUN HWA-YEONG

00:44:05.165 --> 00:44:07.584
-Did you write up this report?
-Yes.

00:44:08.209 --> 00:44:09.919
It's like a martial arts novel.
How is this real?

00:44:10.003 --> 00:44:11.379
I don't believe it all, either.

00:44:12.755 --> 00:44:15.049
But why come to the entertainment desk
at a sister paper

00:44:15.133 --> 00:44:17.927
instead of the culture desk
at the main paper?

00:44:18.011 --> 00:44:19.095
Isn't it obvious?

00:44:19.971 --> 00:44:21.264
They wanted her gone.

00:44:24.100 --> 00:44:25.477
Let's have a meeting.

00:44:25.560 --> 00:44:26.978
-Now?
-Pardon?

00:44:29.772 --> 00:44:30.732
See you later.

00:44:35.987 --> 00:44:37.697
Your new hair color looks amazing.

00:44:38.364 --> 00:44:39.782
Where did you get it done?

00:44:39.866 --> 00:44:41.701
A hair salon at Cheongdam Intersection.

00:44:42.285 --> 00:44:43.286
Are you new here?

00:44:44.787 --> 00:44:45.830
No.

00:44:46.664 --> 00:44:48.625
-Are you Bahn Soo-jung?
-Yes.

00:44:50.543 --> 00:44:52.420
-How do you know me?
-You have a video, right?

00:44:52.504 --> 00:44:56.591
On Friday, February 20th,
you went to entertain some VIPs

00:44:56.674 --> 00:44:58.927
and took a video on your phone,
hoping it might pay off.

00:45:01.137 --> 00:45:02.597
-Who are you?
-Me?

00:45:03.932 --> 00:45:04.891
I'm a reporter.

00:45:06.935 --> 00:45:07.894
Hey, Chief.

00:45:09.437 --> 00:45:10.605
I got a scoop.

00:45:16.319 --> 00:45:17.362
We hit 28%!

00:45:17.445 --> 00:45:21.533
Our ratings were close to 30%
over the course

00:45:21.616 --> 00:45:23.493
of four whole seasons!

00:45:23.576 --> 00:45:25.870
I said 30%!

00:45:25.954 --> 00:45:30.083
Thanks to Good Detective Kang Pil-gu,
my production company bought a building!

00:45:30.166 --> 00:45:33.378
The TV stations said
making dramas wasn't profitable,

00:45:33.461 --> 00:45:36.422
so they almost shut down
that entire business.

00:45:36.506 --> 00:45:40.051
You can say that Kang Pil-gu
brought us back from the brink.

00:45:40.134 --> 00:45:41.386
This might sound funny coming from me,

00:45:41.469 --> 00:45:43.221
but Kang Pil-gu saved a lot of lives.

00:45:43.304 --> 00:45:44.389
Exactly!

00:45:44.472 --> 00:45:47.267
That's why we need
dramas like this to continue.

00:45:47.350 --> 00:45:49.811
Remember that old drama, Country Diaries?

00:45:49.894 --> 00:45:52.814
This drama needs to go on
for 10 to 20 years as well!

00:45:52.897 --> 00:45:56.192
Look at American dramas,
like CSI and NCSI.

00:45:56.276 --> 00:45:59.696
They have spin-offs based in Las Vegas,
Miami, and New York!

00:45:59.779 --> 00:46:03.950
Add them all up, and you can't even count
how many seasons there are!

00:46:04.033 --> 00:46:07.620
What's to stop Kang Pil-gu from running
for 10 or even 20 seasons?

00:46:07.704 --> 00:46:09.205
You're absolutely right.

00:46:09.289 --> 00:46:13.209
But all of that depends on
what our leading man decides to do.

00:46:24.095 --> 00:46:27.098
Are you saying
I have to play a detective until I die?

00:46:27.181 --> 00:46:31.144
Even Gil Grissom
from CSI: Vegas left the series

00:46:31.227 --> 00:46:32.687
to try something different!

00:46:32.770 --> 00:46:35.023
There's nothing left in my life

00:46:35.106 --> 00:46:37.191
except for Kang Pil-gu!

00:46:37.275 --> 00:46:38.109
I'm done!

00:46:46.701 --> 00:46:48.745
I mean, of course…

00:46:50.455 --> 00:46:51.831
I'd love to do it.

00:46:51.914 --> 00:46:53.916
-Right?
-I knew it.

00:46:54.000 --> 00:46:55.835
Kang Pil-gu forever!

00:46:55.918 --> 00:46:58.504
It's much better to play Kang Pil-gu

00:46:58.588 --> 00:47:01.174
than to be in an iffy rom-com
that only gets 2% ratings.

00:47:01.257 --> 00:47:02.133
Of course.

00:47:03.885 --> 00:47:05.553
-That's much better.
-Exactly.

00:47:06.679 --> 00:47:08.181
But you know,

00:47:08.806 --> 00:47:11.893
-I've been a bit scared these days.
-What?

00:47:11.976 --> 00:47:13.895
If I want to last long as an actor,

00:47:13.978 --> 00:47:15.938
I'm afraid my role as Kang Pil-gu

00:47:16.981 --> 00:47:21.736
-must end here--
-That's because your acting is so good!

00:47:21.819 --> 00:47:24.656
Like those mistresses
you see in soap operas.

00:47:24.739 --> 00:47:27.617
Those actresses get slapped on the back
and cursed at by people on the street.

00:47:27.700 --> 00:47:29.035
It's like a badge of honor.

00:47:29.118 --> 00:47:31.120
-Of course, it is.
-Hello?

00:47:31.204 --> 00:47:32.830
Hello?

00:47:32.914 --> 00:47:35.041
Yes, of course. Excuse me.

00:47:35.875 --> 00:47:37.043
Right.

00:47:37.627 --> 00:47:39.337
Yes.

00:47:39.962 --> 00:47:41.047
Oh, I see.

00:47:49.305 --> 00:47:50.848
Excuse me, where's the restroom?

00:47:50.932 --> 00:47:52.266
The restroom is over there.

00:47:52.809 --> 00:47:54.394
Over there? Thank you.

00:48:06.948 --> 00:48:08.908
Why is the lock broken?

00:48:25.341 --> 00:48:26.217
Darn.

00:48:27.760 --> 00:48:29.929
What if Mr. Lim
absolutely refuses to do it?

00:48:30.012 --> 00:48:32.223
All he'll get right now
are iffy supporting roles.

00:48:32.306 --> 00:48:35.184
Who will give him a role
in a melodrama or rom-com at his age?

00:48:35.268 --> 00:48:36.352
He's stuck with Kang Pil-gu.

00:48:36.436 --> 00:48:39.272
I think he's trying to
negotiate a higher pay.

00:48:39.355 --> 00:48:41.190
So just play along for a bit.

00:48:53.953 --> 00:48:56.205
What? A reporter snuck in?

00:48:56.831 --> 00:48:58.458
What do you mean, a reporter came in?

00:48:58.541 --> 00:49:00.752
Were you not monitoring the guests?

00:49:01.753 --> 00:49:02.628
Wait, excuse me!

00:49:05.006 --> 00:49:05.882
-Hey!
-Hey!

00:49:37.580 --> 00:49:39.040
-What are you doing?
-I'm sorry!

00:49:39.123 --> 00:49:40.500
I'll leave soon. Just be quiet.

00:49:40.583 --> 00:49:42.418
-This is the men's--
-Be quiet!

00:49:45.713 --> 00:49:46.672
What's going on?

00:49:48.257 --> 00:49:50.802
I'm really sorry,
but I'm going to have to step on you.

00:49:53.679 --> 00:49:55.056
My leg! Watch my neck!

00:49:59.560 --> 00:50:00.561
My neck!

00:50:08.319 --> 00:50:10.279
My shoes!

00:50:10.780 --> 00:50:12.698
Hurry up! Give me my shoes!

00:50:12.782 --> 00:50:13.866
-Here.
-I'm sorry.

00:50:13.950 --> 00:50:15.993
I'll cover the cost for your phone.
Call me at 0259-2151.

00:50:16.077 --> 00:50:17.537
Give me a call. I'm really sorry!

00:50:18.037 --> 00:50:19.413
My phone?

00:50:21.082 --> 00:50:22.708
My phone!

00:50:22.792 --> 00:50:23.876
Are you kidding me?

00:50:25.211 --> 00:50:27.129
Seriously?

00:50:29.298 --> 00:50:30.633
Damn it!

00:50:38.099 --> 00:50:39.392
There's a crazy woman here.

00:50:39.475 --> 00:50:42.311
Some crazy woman
came into the restroom and…

00:50:43.104 --> 00:50:44.063
Is she a stalker?

00:50:44.146 --> 00:50:47.191
Anyway, I just got attacked!

00:50:47.275 --> 00:50:48.943
I had an upset stomach
and went to the restroom.

00:50:49.026 --> 00:50:50.736
She came in all of a sudden,
stepped all over me,

00:50:50.820 --> 00:50:52.029
and then disappeared…

00:50:53.030 --> 00:50:54.782
And my phone fell in the toilet--

00:50:54.866 --> 00:50:55.992
You're Kang Pil-gu!

00:50:56.075 --> 00:50:57.618
You're Good Detective Kang Pil-gu, right?

00:51:00.705 --> 00:51:03.332
Who knew I'd see you here, Detective?
It's such an honor!

00:51:03.416 --> 00:51:05.459
I watched every single season.

00:51:06.711 --> 00:51:07.879
Thank you.

00:51:08.796 --> 00:51:09.964
So did someone barge into the restroom?

00:51:12.049 --> 00:51:14.218
No, don't worry about it.

00:51:15.219 --> 00:51:16.304
Go Kang Pil-gu!

00:51:24.478 --> 00:51:26.814
All he'll get right now
are iffy supporting roles.

00:51:26.898 --> 00:51:29.984
Who will give him a role
in a melodrama or rom-com at his age?

00:51:30.067 --> 00:51:31.527
He's stuck with Kang Pil-gu.

00:51:40.661 --> 00:51:42.914
What is it? Are you in a bad mood again?

00:51:42.997 --> 00:51:45.499
I wouldn't have gone there
if I'd known what it was about.

00:51:45.583 --> 00:51:46.959
A private hostess bar, no less.

00:51:47.043 --> 00:51:49.879
I know. That's why I didn't tell you.

00:51:49.962 --> 00:51:50.880
Mr. Hwang.

00:51:52.089 --> 00:51:56.135
I mean it when I say
that I won't play Kang Pil-gu anymore.

00:51:56.636 --> 00:51:59.639
Okay, I got it.
We'll talk about that later.

00:51:59.722 --> 00:52:01.390
Will you be okay at the award ceremony?

00:52:01.474 --> 00:52:04.435
I can tell you're worried,
taking those herbal calming pills.

00:52:05.603 --> 00:52:08.356
Do I have to go to the award ceremony?

00:52:08.439 --> 00:52:09.607
I'm not even getting one.

00:52:13.027 --> 00:52:17.740
You received an award last year,
so now it's your turn to give one.

00:52:17.823 --> 00:52:19.241
I'm sick right now.

00:52:20.576 --> 00:52:22.870
Come on, I'm in pain.

00:52:22.954 --> 00:52:25.456
Fine. Take some more pills.

00:52:35.174 --> 00:52:37.385
Blown away

00:52:38.678 --> 00:52:40.179
In the wind--

00:52:57.446 --> 00:52:58.864
OBTAINED HOSTESS ENTERTAINMENT VIDEO

00:52:58.948 --> 00:53:00.324
NO CIRCUMSTANTIAL EVIDENCE

00:53:10.126 --> 00:53:11.210
WOO YOUNG-SUK, AIDE

00:53:12.628 --> 00:53:14.338
Does Assemblyman Ha
really have nothing to do

00:53:14.422 --> 00:53:16.257
with the redevelopment in Cheongwon City?

00:53:16.340 --> 00:53:19.385
Are you saying his aide
took all that money for himself?

00:53:19.468 --> 00:53:21.512
Mr. Woo, an aide
to Assemblyman Ha Gee-wan,

00:53:21.595 --> 00:53:22.805
was found dead.

00:53:22.888 --> 00:53:24.890
Officials are considering
the possibility of suicide.

00:53:24.974 --> 00:53:28.019
Mr. Woo's family
wants to avoid escalating the issue.

00:53:28.102 --> 00:53:29.854
So if you keep poking around,

00:53:29.937 --> 00:53:32.940
a lot of people will get hurt, understand?

00:53:56.589 --> 00:53:58.591
WOO YOUNG-SUK

00:54:04.930 --> 00:54:06.307
You're here again, Ms. Wi.

00:54:08.059 --> 00:54:09.018
It's been a long time.

00:54:09.643 --> 00:54:11.187
It's already been seven years.

00:54:11.812 --> 00:54:14.398
You really don't have to come anymore.

00:54:15.524 --> 00:54:16.984
Thank you for everything.

00:54:19.695 --> 00:54:20.780
It's not over yet.

00:54:22.031 --> 00:54:24.658
I'll find out what Mr. Woo wanted to say

00:54:25.326 --> 00:54:27.787
and how his death was staged as a suicide.

00:54:30.414 --> 00:54:32.166
I'll get to the bottom of it.

00:54:32.666 --> 00:54:34.043
EUNSEONGILBO

00:54:42.218 --> 00:54:43.427
My apologies, sir.

00:54:43.511 --> 00:54:45.763
I trust you'll take care of that reporter.

00:54:45.846 --> 00:54:47.473
Yes, sir. Understood.

00:54:49.934 --> 00:54:50.768
A sports tabloid?

00:54:53.354 --> 00:54:55.022
Get back to work, everyone.

00:54:56.148 --> 00:54:58.192
Just work the entertainment desk
for a year, okay?

00:54:58.275 --> 00:54:59.151
The entertainment desk?

00:54:59.985 --> 00:55:02.530
You're bumping me to the sports tabloid,
and not even for a transfer?

00:55:03.072 --> 00:55:05.366
But you saw that video, Chief.
It's a major scoop!

00:55:05.449 --> 00:55:07.201
The video barely shows any faces,

00:55:07.284 --> 00:55:09.745
and there aren't any audible voices,
so how is that a scoop?

00:55:09.829 --> 00:55:12.414
I understand why you want to
sweep this under the rug.

00:55:12.498 --> 00:55:15.584
But let's be honest, Chief.
You recognized who it was.

00:55:16.293 --> 00:55:17.503
Hey.

00:55:17.586 --> 00:55:20.339
One wrong move,
and your petty desire for fame

00:55:21.048 --> 00:55:22.258
will land us in hot water.

00:55:22.883 --> 00:55:24.927
Do you want to see
the entire political desk get wiped out?

00:55:25.010 --> 00:55:27.471
Do you cherry-pick articles
to write for your petty paycheck?

00:55:27.555 --> 00:55:28.848
What the hell did you say?

00:55:28.931 --> 00:55:31.183
You just crossed the line.
How dare you say that?

00:55:33.561 --> 00:55:34.979
I'm a political reporter.

00:55:35.896 --> 00:55:37.398
I refuse to be forced

00:55:38.274 --> 00:55:39.525
to work the entertainment desk.

00:55:43.571 --> 00:55:45.114
That little brat…

00:55:46.115 --> 00:55:47.533
But why is she coming?

00:55:47.616 --> 00:55:50.661
They've been looking for ways
to get rid of her for a while.

00:55:50.744 --> 00:55:52.163
She's addicted to work

00:55:52.246 --> 00:55:54.081
and has absolutely no social skills.

00:55:54.165 --> 00:55:55.583
I hear she's really unlikeable.

00:55:55.666 --> 00:55:57.293
Hey, we're not a damage control team!

00:55:58.419 --> 00:56:01.463
That's enough. Stop making a big deal
out of someone joining us.

00:56:02.047 --> 00:56:04.717
How come none of you seem worried
after writing such a lousy story today?

00:56:06.552 --> 00:56:08.637
The Geumsang Arts Awards is today, right?

00:56:09.221 --> 00:56:12.641
Find out who wore similar dresses
or who was a fashion disaster,

00:56:12.725 --> 00:56:14.351
and write it up before the ceremony.

00:56:14.935 --> 00:56:19.190
The battle of the red carpet dresses.
Who will be the winners and losers?

00:56:19.273 --> 00:56:25.112
First, the organizer of this ceremony
and the one who made today possible.

00:56:25.196 --> 00:56:27.656
Chairman Lee Dae-ho, a young leader

00:56:27.740 --> 00:56:29.742
-guiding the industry forward.
-Chairman!

00:56:29.825 --> 00:56:32.036
-With an aura that could rival an actor,
-Chairman!

00:56:32.119 --> 00:56:33.329
he's stepped onto the red carpet.

00:56:34.580 --> 00:56:35.789
Chairman Lee Dae-ho!

00:56:36.373 --> 00:56:37.541
I'm from the political desk!

00:56:38.125 --> 00:56:39.376
Sir! Chairman Lee!

00:56:41.212 --> 00:56:43.297
Excuse me, Chairman Lee!

00:56:44.048 --> 00:56:45.466
I'm from the political desk!

00:56:46.008 --> 00:56:47.885
Sir! Chairman Lee!

00:56:49.178 --> 00:56:53.641
Don't miss out on the man making
an appearance on the red carpet now.

00:56:54.225 --> 00:56:58.187
He's successfully led the drama,
Good Detective Kang Pil-gu.

00:56:58.270 --> 00:57:00.940
Last year, he won the Best Actor award

00:57:01.023 --> 00:57:04.360
-at the Geumsang Arts Awards…
-Chairman Lee Dae-ho!

00:57:04.443 --> 00:57:05.861
Please comment on
the retaliatory personnel decisions

00:57:05.945 --> 00:57:07.321
taking place at Eunseongilbo!

00:57:08.113 --> 00:57:09.114
Where are you from?

00:57:09.198 --> 00:57:10.324
I'm Wi Jeong-sin from the political desk!

00:57:10.407 --> 00:57:12.785
You've been avoiding my calls
and refusing to meet me,

00:57:12.868 --> 00:57:14.662
so I was forced to come here!

00:57:14.745 --> 00:57:16.080
-Let's talk next time.
-Sir!

00:57:16.163 --> 00:57:18.123
Please cancel my personnel transfer!

00:57:18.207 --> 00:57:19.458
We'll talk next time.

00:57:21.001 --> 00:57:21.961
Excuse me.

00:58:13.887 --> 00:58:15.097
Mr. Lim!

00:59:22.915 --> 00:59:25.209
SPECIAL THANKS TO OH YEON-SEO
FOR HER APPEARANCE

00:59:28.962 --> 00:59:30.422
Of course, I'm struggling.

00:59:30.506 --> 00:59:32.424
You must have a bad memory.

00:59:32.508 --> 00:59:34.593
We actually met in a very dramatic way.

00:59:34.676 --> 00:59:37.805
There's no way this woman is a reporter.

00:59:38.263 --> 00:59:39.848
You can't embarrass a reporter like that!

00:59:39.932 --> 00:59:41.975
-Do you want to bury Lim Hyeon-jun?
-Yes!

00:59:42.059 --> 00:59:45.187
Everyone has dirt to hide,
and where there's smoke, there's fire.

00:59:45.270 --> 00:59:48.774
Reporter Wi Jeong-sin will not be allowed
to take part in this interview.

00:59:48.857 --> 00:59:51.026
Groveling at my feet
wouldn't have been enough!

00:59:51.110 --> 00:59:52.778
I'm just returning the favor.

00:59:52.861 --> 00:59:55.489
This reporter is a damn lunatic!

00:59:58.867 --> 01:00:00.869
Subtitle: Jenny Kim